sources.title: Vengeance of Rannah
sources.description: Insurance Agent Ted Sanders (Bob Custer) has been called in to investigate a robbery and murder. A deputy (Ed Cassidy) also arrives to investigate. But unknown to Ted, the Deputy is a fake and actually part of the gang. The fake plants some of the money in Ted's room so he can arrest him. Then with the help of the gang he plans to finish Ted off.

sources.title: Vengeance of Rannah (1936) BOB CUSTER
sources.description:
Stars: Bob Custer, John Elliott, Rin Tin Tin Jr.
Director: Bernard B. Ray

Insurance Agent Ted Sanders has been called in to investigate a robbery and murder. A deputy also arrives to investigate. But unknown to Ted, the Deputy is a fake and actually part of the gang. The fake plants some of the money in Ted's room so he can arrest him. Then with the help of the gang he plans to finish Ted off.

TRIVIA: Born Raymond Anthony Glenn on October 18, 1898, in Frankfort, Kentucky, Bob Custer made his film debut in the 1920s and quickly became a popular figure in the B-Western genre. His rugged good looks and ability to perform his own stunts helped him stand out among the many cowboy stars of the era.
